exchange for 37 percent of the satellite broadcaster. Also,
Echostar will carry Fox programs. Echostar sued the News Corp. last
year for backing out of plans to buy 50 percent of the company; it
now says it will drop the suit if this deal is completed.
Meanwhile, in October, Primestar dropped its proposed $1.1 billion
purchase of American Sky Broadcasting, jointly owned by the News
Corp. and MCI, because of regulatory hurdles.
