the stand. By Joel Brinkley.
</P>
<P>
   VOLVO-CUTBACKS (Rome) _ Volvo will cut 5,300 jobs, or about 7
percent of its labor force, as it tries to save 3 billion kronor,
or $367 million, a year. Volvo, which is battling recession in Asia
and slower growth in Europe and the United States, becomes the
latest car maker to announce job cuts in Europe; Rover Group plans
to cut 2,500 workers and Ford aims to eliminate 2,300 in Belgium.
By John Tagliabue.
</P>
<P>
   MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ The daily marketplace column.
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ At midday, the industrial average was off
105 points, or 1.1 percent, and the Nasdaq index was down 36
points, or 1.8 percent. Elsewhere, prices fell 1.2 percent in Tokyo
and 3.2 percent in Hong Kong. They were off 2.6 percent in
Frankfurt, 1.2 percent in London, 3 percent in Brazil and 1.4
percent in Mexico. On the American debt market, the long bond was
up 27/32 point, with the yield at 5.11 percent. By Kenneth N.
Gilpin.
