<HEADLINE>
`ZORRO' HAS PIZZAZ, BUT; `BEFORE TIME VI' A LOSER 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES:  &UR; ``The Mask of Zorro''  &LR; _ Antonio Banderas stars
in this splendidly mounted retelling of the foxy hero's legend.
It's got splash and pizazz with a stunningly choreographed duel and
enough special effects to fill the Enterprise. But it's rather
hollow at the center, and the cuts between Anthony Hopkins's
close-ups and long shots make it obvious that a stuntman is doing
the hard stuff. Frankly, we prefer the 1940 black-and-white version
starring Tyrone Power and directed by that underrated genius Rouben
Mamoulian. It's also available on home video.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Land Before Time VI''  &LR; _ V too many.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``The Last Seduction 2''  &LR; _ John Dahl's sexy, provocative
original, starring Linda Fiorentino as a lady on the lam, was
brilliant; this sequel, with Joan Severance, is dull and
repetitive.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Woman in the Dunes'' &LR;  _ Hiroshi Teshigahara directed this
1964 Oscar winner (for best foreign-language film) with tough
artistry. The parable of a doomed couple trapped in sand dunes
resonates as a timeless allegory.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
---- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   SILENTS PLEASE: ``The Chap-lin Mutuals: Remastered'' is coming
out on Jan. 12 in three volumes from Kino on Video. The short
subjects include ``The Immigrant,'' ``The Adventurer,'' ``The
Cure,'' ``Easy Street,'' ``The Count,'' ``The Vagabond,'' ``The
Fireman,'' ``Behind the Screen,'' ``One A.M.,'' ``The Pawnshop,''
``The Floorwalker,'' and ``The Rink.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS:  &UR; Dec. 8:  &LR; ``The Parent Trap,'' ``Lured,''
``Alibi,'' ``Double Edge,'' ``Sour Grapes,'' ``Urban Safari,'' ``It
Happened Tomorrow.''  &UR; Dec. 15: &LR;  ``The Boxer,'' ``Madeline,'' ``How
I Spent My Summer Vacation,'' ``Half Baked,'' ``The Strauss
Family,'' ``A Friend of the Deceased,'' ``Indiscreet.''  &UR; Dec. 18:
 &LR; ``Air Bud: Golden Receiver,'' ``Summer of the Monkeys.''  &UR; Dec. 22:
 &LR; ``Blade,'' ``BASEketball,'' ``The Secret of Nimh 2,'' ``Billy's
Hollywood Screen Kiss,'' ``Random Encounter,'' ``Act of War.''
 &UR; Jan. 5:  &LR; ``Out of Sight,'' ``Every Mother's Fear,'' ``Scarred
City.''  &UR; Jan. 12:  &LR; ``Love and Death on Long Island,''
``Fireworks,'' ``Buffalo Island,'' ``Wubbulous World of Dr.
