won't win. Banks will boost checking fees so high that eventually,
we'll switch to electronic-payment vouchers. And the deregulation
of electricity, natural gas, phone service and cable will bring
more bills to pay with these more sophisticated devices. Our only
hope may be duct tape. Maybe if we can wrap the tape tight enough,
our heads won't burst. (Geewax, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) (k,
f) MOVED
