   FBC-TENN-MSTATE _ After struggling early in the season, some
Tennessee fans and opposing coaches began to wonder if Tee Martin
could handle the job as the Volunteers' starting QB. But Martin
silenced the critics by leading the Vols to an impressive victory
at Georgia and later set an NCAA record for consecutive completions
in a win over South Carolina. Martin leads the unbeaten and
top-ranked Vols into Saturday's SEC championship game against
Mississippi State and a victory will likely give the team the
national title. For a player who struggled early, Martin is only
two wins away from a feat that his highly publicized predecessor,
Peyton Manning, never accomplished. (Wilkinson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
