<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-AIDSVAX-CRITERIA-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Criteria for vaccine volunteers
 &HT;    By Lillian Lee Kim
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Volunteers for the AIDSVAX trials should contact the AIDS
Research Consortium of Atlanta at 404-876-2317, Ext. 333, or look
up the Internet site at http://arca.home.mindspring
</P>
<P>
   .com. VaxGen's Web site is http://www.vaxgen.com.
</P>
<P>
   All volunteers must be between18 and 60, and must show evidence
of a negative HIV test within the past 90 days.
</P>
<P>
   Men: Must be gay or bisexual and have had anal intercourse
within the past 12 months.
</P>
<P>
   Women: Must fit one of two categories: (1) Partners of
HIV-positive men or, (2) have had sex with more than one man in the
past 12 months and have had a documented sexually transmitted
disease during that period.
</P>
<P>
   Excluded are:
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Men who have been in monogamous relationships with other
HIV-negative men for more than a year.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  People with past or current IV drug use.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Those who have had diseases that suppress their immune
systems.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Those who have previously received an HIV vaccine.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Those who have taken experimental drugs within the past four
weeks.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Pregnant women.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
