<P>
   CENSUS-SAMPLING (Washington) _ Supreme Court gets between the
warring White House and GOP House on the hot topic of how to count
the 2000 Census. It was notably uncomfortable being there. By Mary
Leonard. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   HOUSE-IMPEACH (Washington) -- Former US attorney general Elliot
L. Richardson says the House should censure President Clinton and
reject the effort to impeach him. By Bob Hohler. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   TITANIC-RIVETS (Boston) -- New research on the latest pieces of
the Titanic, brought up by an expedition last summer, seem to
confirm a theory that it was defective rivets, made from inferior
iron, that caused the supposedly unsinkable ship to sink. By David
L. Chandler. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   LOOTED-ART (Boston) -- Museum of Fine Arts seeks to confirm
revelations that a Monet painting was confiscated by the Nazis from
a prominent French Jewish art collector. By Brian MacQuarrie. 800
words.
</P>
<P>
