<P>
   BUS-CRASH-FOLLOW (Seattle) Police confirm the scenario: A .380
automatic was the murder/suicide weapon in the fatal bus crash in
Seattle last week. The suspect, Silas Cool walked up to the driver
and fired two shots. The first was the fatal shot, in the arm and
through the chest cavity. The second shot also was in the
chest.There are conflicting reports of whether he had any
conversation with the driver or just walked up and shot.Cool's own
wound went right through his temple, through the brain, and ``most
likely killed him instantly.'' Police yesterday searched his
apartment and found a collection of knives (switchblades, hunting,
carving, etc.) and two pellet guns, plus ``a lot of pornography.''
</P>
<P>
   By Vanessa Ho and Mike Barber. (story will move in the ``a''
category)
