<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Tuesday, Dec. 1 and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Jeremy Bagott at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   UNIVERSAL-SILVER (Los Angeles) _ The flops just keep coming and
so do the resignations. Universal Pictures Chairman Casey Silver
departs following the disappointing opening of its pricey ``Babe:
Pig in the City.'' The ax has now fallen on half a dozen top-level
Universal executives since last spring as Seagram chief Edgar
Bronfman Jr. asserts more control over Unviersal's operations. By
Dave McNary (Will move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
   FIDELITY-SHAKEUP (Los Angeles) _ Bank Plus Corp. said it has
completed a management shake-up that it expects to save it $1.2
million annual and another $4.6 million in one-time expenses. The
parent of Fidelity Federal Bank said it has promoted three
executives and rejiggered the company's employee stock in response
to a dismal third quarter which saw the firm lose $60 million. By
Ben Sullivan. (Will move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
