<P>
   Lead story:
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH (Washington) _ Republicans on the House Judiciary
Committee take renewed interest in President Clinton's 1996
campaign finances and plan to subpoena the director of the FBI and
the Justice Department's former senior prosecutor for campaign
finance abuses. With the impeachment inquiry moving into its final
stages, Republican aides say the committee will vote on the
subpoenas Tuesday. By Eric Schmitt and Alison Mitchell. (We plan to
move the story by 9 p.m. ET in ``w'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   Reefer to RENO-ICKES.
</P>
<P>
   Top center story:
</P>
